# Running things from the terminal — {{ project_name }}

Canonical entry points are the **`make` targets** (defined in `Makefile`). They
wrap the underlying commands so you don't have to remember them. But `make` is
not installed on every machine (Windows often lacks it) — so this file also lists
the **make-less equivalents** to run the exact same commands directly.

> Check `~/.claude/environment.md` (auto-probed once per machine) to see whether
> `make`, `rg`, `Rscript`, `quarto`, … are present **on this machine** before you
> reach for them. Don't re-verify each session — read the cache.

## Entry points (prefer these)

| Goal | With `make` | Make-less equivalent (same command) |
|---|---|---|
{% if analysis_stack == 'r' -%}
| Restore env | `make setup` | `Rscript -e 'if (file.exists("renv.lock")) renv::restore(prompt = FALSE) else renv::init()'` |
| Lint | `make lint` | `Rscript -e 'lintr::lint_dir()'` |
| Run pipeline | `make test` / `make all` | `Rscript -e 'targets::tar_make()'` |
| Rebuild from zero | `make reset` then `make all` | `Rscript -e 'targets::tar_destroy(ask = FALSE)'` then `tar_make()` |
{% elif analysis_stack == 'python' -%}
| Sync env | `make setup` | `uv sync` |
| Lint | `make lint` | `uv run ruff check .` |
| Test | `make test` | `uv run pytest` |
{% else -%}
| (no analysis stack selected — nothing to build) | | |
{% endif -%}
| Check placeholders | `make placeholders` | `python scripts/check_placeholders.py` |
| Rebuild indices | `make reindex` | `python scripts/reindex.py` |

